Hi,
I was curious if the Kraken’s currently support any type of planetary gearboxes? A university club that I am a part on have already invested in the Sports Gearbox ecosystem from AM mostly for CIMs, but we got our hands on some Krakens and looking to incorporate them.

I am a recent alum, so I am a little rusty on the products coming with Kraken within the FRC community. Upon a little research tho, the AM sport gearbox for Falcons require 16 Tooth 0.7 Module pinions which as far as I know is not available for Krakens. (Also, obviously requires the short Falcon shaft, I don’t know how that would be viable at all cause as far as I know Kraken has an “Non-replaceable output shaft”. I don’t know if there could be a workaround for that.) @Andy_Baker Any plans on selling such a Kraken Pinion soon on AM maybe?

I looked at VP and Max Planetary options, but I don’t think they support an input stage for Krakens right now. Could someone correct me if I am wrong with anything up till now?

Is there any other way to get a planetary gearbox option for Krakens or is it just plate gearboxes like the ones WCP sells?
